<paragraph blockId="16.[121,1089,1602,1664]" pageId="16" pageNumber="355">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giron &amp; Franz" authorityYear="2010" box="[121,291,1602,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Apodrosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="artus">
<emphasis box="[121,291,1602,1628]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="355">Apodrosus artus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known to occur in the Central Cordillera at an altitudinal range of 1000–1150 m, in the La Vega province of the Dominican Republic, northeast of Pico
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[121,1089,147,209]" pageId="17" pageNumber="356">
Duarte, the highest elevation of the Hispaniola (
<figureCitation box="[667,769,147,174]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="61.[121,154,1637,1659]" captionTargetBox="[125,1085,146,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[125,1085,146,1615]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Fig. 18. Occurrences of Apodrosus species in (A) the Bahamas (Grand Bahama and Andros Island) and (B) Hispaniola, Mona Island, and the Turks and Caicos Islands." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3764604" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3764604/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="356">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
